articles.title: Your Guide to October's 'Ring of Fire' Solar Eclipse - Gizmodo
articles.description: The annular solar eclipse will be visible across North, Central, and South America on October 14. It’s the last one for the U.S. until 2039.
articles.content:
The Americas are in for an astronomical treat on October 14, as an annular solar eclipse, known as the ring of fire, will be visible across vast swaths of the Western Hemisphere.
